						               													<description>In Divine Corruption: Rebirth, you play as a human who&amp;rsquo;s starting their second and final life in Aurae, the kingdom and paradise reserved for celestial beings. Selected by those heavenly rulers to serve as a lowly slave, it&amp;rsquo;s up to you to do everything you can to prove your value to your masters, so that you too can join the celestial caste. But remember that there are only two ways a slave&amp;rsquo;s life can end: in coronation among the celestials or in death.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this semi-cooperative game, every outcome is possible. You can all be victorious and live happily among celestials or you can all finish on the scaffold. Only you can decide your path, will you cooperate with your peers or will you try to be the only one to live?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every move, every action, every card you play have consequences. Help a fellow comrade accomplish a mission and he can help you achieve your goal but, take the renown of a more ambitious fellow player and see how fast revenge will come.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn, the active player chooses the mission he wants to do. He can either do it alone if he has enough profession or ask another player and share credits. By doing a mission you gain renown but the more you are, the less you gain.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then, any player can play cards from their hands. They can either be good with you and help you out or they can try to steal your points or your own cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;People will do missions and amass points until one if them gets 75 points. At this point you have only a few turn before the game ends and all of those with 75 will have won, all the other will lose their heads and die for good this time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
